description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Specialist Orthoptist to join our dedicated team of 3 Orthoptists, 4 Optometrists, 4 Ophthalmic Technicians and 6 Consultant Ophthalmologists including a Paediatric Ophthalmologist with an interest in Ocular Motility Disorders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based within the Royal Glamorgan Hospital at Llantrisant, the post holder will experience a varied &amp; complex caseload including referrals from Neurology, Endocrinology and Oral Surgery. Consultant led Squint and Paediatric Ophthalmology Clinics with further Orthoptic sessions based at a local Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a strong emphasis on Orthoptic led shared care for paediatric Orthoptic cases. Cwm Taf Morgannwg University Health Board is located in the South Wales Valleys with easy access to the busy metropolitan city of Cardiff, the beautiful South Wales Coast and the Brecon Beacons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mark Deacon - Head of Orthoptic Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mark.Deacon@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01685 728131&lt;/p&gt;
